    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Refers to the style of European and American architecture and fine and decorative arts between the mid-18th century and the mid-19th century inspired by archaeological discoveries in the Mediterranean and Near East and characterized by the imitation of Greek and Roman forms and motifs.  Also considered a reaction to Rococo opulence, Neoclassical works are often linear, symmetrical, and even severe.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000099620/Legacy AAT data</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Se refiere al estilo de arquitectura americana y europea y bellas y decorativas artes entre mediados del siglo XVIII y mediados del siglo XIX inspirado en los descubrimientos arqueológicos en el Mediterráneo y Cercano Oriente y que se caracteriza por la imitación de formas y motivos griegos y romanos. También considerado una reacción a la opulencia del Rococó, las obras Neoclásicas son a menudo lineales, simétricas e incluso severas.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Spanish</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000131/CDBP-SNPC</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000051034/TAA database (2000-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Te gebruiken voor laat 18e- en 19e-eeuwse kunst en architectuur die de beginselen van het classicisme volgt. Gebruik 'neoklassiek' voor architectuur en ornamentatie van het eind van de 18e tot het begin van de 20e eeuw, die vrij sterk is gebaseerd op oude klassieke vormen.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000205/AAT-Ned</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000113770/AAT-Ned (1994-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000099099/Van Dale groot woordenboek (1994)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>指十八世紀中葉至十九世紀中葉期間，歐洲與美洲的建築、美術和裝飾藝術風格，受到地中海和近東的考古發現所啟發，其特色為模仿希臘和羅馬的形式和母題。也被視為對洛可可華麗風格的回應，新古典主義的作品通常為線性、對稱，甚至過於簡樸。</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Chinese (traditional)</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000250/AS-Academia Sinica</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000079740/AS-Academia Sinica data (2014-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Refere-se ao estilo de arquitetura e artes finas e decorativas europeias e americanas entre meados do século 18 e meados do século 19, inspirado nas descobertas arqueológicas no Mediterrâneo e no Oriente Próximo e caracterizado pela imitação de formas e motivos gregos e romanos. Também considerados uma reação à opulência do Rococó, os trabalhos neoclássicos costumam ser lineares, simétricos e até mesmo severos. </Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Portuguese</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000316/CVAA-BR</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
